      <originalsloc id="aspace_1d1ff714aef9a154e9d392a749f18f26">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection can be located in the Jerome New Frank Papers (MS 222).   The papers consist of correspondence, legal material (including opinions, decisions, calendars, memoranda, and other papers), writings, speeches, Yale course materials, and family and personal papers of Jerome N. Frank, lawyer, government official during the New Deal, author, legal philosopher, teacher, and federal judge.</p>
         <p>HM 243 only consists of the annotated transcript of Jerome Frank's Columbia Oral History interview</p>  
